In article <E11WHGk-0001w8-00@the-village.bc.nu> you wrote:
> ARP Replies are unicast
Yes, but Who-Has ARP Requests are Broadcasted and have the ip-address of the
host who is asking for it. That wont catch all cases but can give a good
indicaton of an active host claimng to have the same address as yours.
